---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Breadcrumb from "@/components/site/Breadcrumb.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="What learn.msp.au is, who it's for, and how to use it."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 py-8">
    <Breadcrumb items={[{ href: "/", label: "Home" }, { label: "About" }]} />

    <header class="mt-6 mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight">About</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-muted-foreground">
        Free, opinionated training for MSP technicians — no accounts, no
        tracking, just the critical path.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="lesson-prose">
      <h2>What this is</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>learn.msp.au</strong> takes engineers and helpdesk staff at
        Managed Service Providers along the critical training path required
        to do 90% of their job for typical clients — across the products you
        actually use every day.
      </p>
      <p>
        Education is broken into three layered tiers per vendor:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Beginner</strong> — fundamentals, daily UI, the most
          common workflows.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Intermediate</strong> — design decisions, troubleshooting,
          edge cases. Builds on Beginner without repeating it.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Advanced</strong> — architecture, integrations,
          escalations, performance tuning. Builds on Intermediate without
          repeating it.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What it's not</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>It's not a vendor's official documentation. Always cross-check critical settings.</li>
        <li>It's not a certification. There are no badges to print.</li>
        <li>It's not exhaustive — it's the <em>critical path</em>, not the manual.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How to use it</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Pick a vendor, start at the level that matches you, work the lessons in order.</li>
        <li>Hover any underlined term for a definition; click for the full glossary entry.</li>
        <li>Inline checkpoints are short — answer them honestly; wrong answers explain themselves.</li>
        <li>End-of-course quizzes randomise questions from a larger pool; retake until they feel easy.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        No accounts. No cookies. Your lesson completion and quiz scores live in
        your browser's localStorage and never leave your device. You can export
        a JSON snapshot from <a href="/settings/">Settings</a>, take it to a
        new browser, and import it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Site analytics use Cloudflare's cookieless web analytics — pageviews
        only, no fingerprinting, no third parties.
      </p>

      <h2>Contributing</h2>
      <p>
        See a mistake? Found a vendor UI that's changed? Want a new vendor
        covered? The site source is open — open an issue or PR.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
